name: Donald Sutherland
summary: Sadly, actor Donald Sutherland has passed away at the age of 88. The Canadian-born actor was known for his roles in "MASH", "Klute", and "The Hunger Games." Sutherland was born in St. John, New Brunswick, Canada in 1935. He began his acting career in the early 1960s, appearing in small roles in television and film. He got his start in radio before making a name for himself as a film and television actor. Sutherland's career spanned over six decades, during which he starred in over 100 films and television shows. He is considered one of the greatest Canadian actors of all time.

summary: Jessica Alba's newest film, "Trigger Warning," has garnered mixed reviews upon its release on Netflix. The film follows Alba as a retired soldier who becomes entangled in a war against domestic criminals. Despite its flaws, some reviewers have found the film to be an enjoyable and entertaining watch, while others have found it to be a stale and unoriginal action thriller. "Trigger Warning" has received the lowest Rotten Tomatoes score of any film released in 2023, but it remains to be seen whether this will affect its popularity with audiences.
